Constructor Detail

IteratingCollectionEdit

public IteratingCollectionEdit(java.lang.Object context,
                               java.util.List<?> values,
                               IteratingCollectionEdit.CycleBehaviour cycleBehavior)
Create an IEdit that will, each time edit is called, set a specified property on the current dto to the next available value from a list. The specified property is accessed via an IPropertyAccess which is created by passing in the context object to the currently configured IPropertyAccessFactory.

Parameters:
context - An object used for specifying which property to edit.

This context is passed to the IPropertyAccessFactory

values - A list of values that will be used by this edit.
cycleBehavior - The behaviour that this edit will exhibit after all values have been used.
